metadata.name: The Nothing
metadata.description:
I used to think my demons weren’t me.  
That they were this darkness I needed to drown.  
Suffocate.  
Before they engulfed me.  
Once the Nothing took over and they became my solace in the void.  
We spoke of our rage. 
Our grief. 
Our sadness.  
To think there was a moment where I thought my demons weren’t me.
